WEBVTT

00:00:07.516 --> 00:00:15.500 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:00:26.516 --> 00:00:34.246 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:00:34.746 --> 00:00:36.436 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So hello everyone.

00:00:36.656 --> 00:00:38.086 A:middle
My name is Doug LeMoine.

00:00:38.676 --> 00:00:40.596 A:middle
My background is in interaction

00:00:40.596 --> 00:00:41.246 A:middle
design.

00:00:41.316 --> 00:00:43.266 A:middle
And here at Apple I'm on a team

00:00:43.266 --> 00:00:45.046 A:middle
of people who works with

00:00:45.046 --> 00:00:46.206 A:middle
developers like you.

00:00:46.376 --> 00:00:49.146 A:middle
As a designer I focus on user

00:00:49.146 --> 00:00:51.296 A:middle
interfaces and the ideas to

00:00:51.296 --> 00:00:54.636 A:middle
deliver great user experiences

00:00:54.696 --> 00:00:56.226 A:middle
to the people who use your apps.

00:00:57.146 --> 00:00:58.976 A:middle
Today I'm here to talk about

00:00:59.606 --> 00:01:00.256 A:middle
intent.

00:00:59.606 --> 00:01:00.256 A:middle
intent.

00:01:01.436 --> 00:01:03.386 A:middle
I think there's a thread running

00:01:03.386 --> 00:01:05.476 A:middle
through great apps and really

00:01:05.476 --> 00:01:06.566 A:middle
great products.

00:01:06.566 --> 00:01:08.586 A:middle
And it has to do with a

00:01:08.586 --> 00:01:11.556 A:middle
conscious focus on people, on

00:01:11.556 --> 00:01:14.476 A:middle
humans, and what they want and

00:01:14.536 --> 00:01:16.266 A:middle
what they really need.

00:01:18.056 --> 00:01:19.356 A:middle
So I'm going to talk about

00:01:19.386 --> 00:01:21.096 A:middle
focusing on the person you want

00:01:21.096 --> 00:01:21.616 A:middle
to serve.

00:01:22.046 --> 00:01:24.726 A:middle
And I'm going to focus on being

00:01:24.726 --> 00:01:25.586 A:middle
intentional.

00:01:25.996 --> 00:01:27.716 A:middle
The intent that I'm interested

00:01:27.716 --> 00:01:29.236 A:middle
in talking about today is less

00:01:29.236 --> 00:01:32.326 A:middle
about a specific design vision

00:01:32.326 --> 00:01:36.376 A:middle
or a specific outcome and more

00:01:36.376 --> 00:01:37.756 A:middle
on a mindset.

00:01:38.266 --> 00:01:40.286 A:middle
How to keep a sharp focus on

00:01:40.286 --> 00:01:41.896 A:middle
those people that you're trying

00:01:41.896 --> 00:01:44.976 A:middle
to reach and create apps that

00:01:44.976 --> 00:01:45.756 A:middle
feel simple.

00:01:45.826 --> 00:01:48.176 A:middle
And when an app feels simple

00:01:49.556 --> 00:01:52.566 A:middle
users perceive it as natural, an

00:01:52.566 --> 00:01:54.126 A:middle
extension of what they know.

00:01:54.126 --> 00:01:55.896 A:middle
It feels like it arises from

00:01:55.896 --> 00:01:58.486 A:middle
their experience and it flows

00:01:58.486 --> 00:02:00.316 A:middle
naturally from what they expect.

00:01:58.486 --> 00:02:00.316 A:middle
naturally from what they expect.

00:02:01.886 --> 00:02:04.196 A:middle
So I know simple and natural are

00:02:04.196 --> 00:02:06.546 A:middle
sort of designer cliches, we say

00:02:06.546 --> 00:02:07.796 A:middle
this stuff all the time.

00:02:08.166 --> 00:02:09.256 A:middle
Like, what do we mean?

00:02:10.096 --> 00:02:11.306 A:middle
I think these terms are

00:02:11.306 --> 00:02:13.846 A:middle
shorthand for discussing

00:02:13.846 --> 00:02:15.516 A:middle
qualities of apps that create

00:02:15.576 --> 00:02:17.836 A:middle
feelings of comfort and

00:02:17.836 --> 00:02:18.706 A:middle
confidence.

00:02:19.726 --> 00:02:21.586 A:middle
When people feel comfortable and

00:02:21.586 --> 00:02:23.626 A:middle
confident, when we understand

00:02:23.626 --> 00:02:25.276 A:middle
how a thing works, we can move

00:02:25.366 --> 00:02:27.176 A:middle
through it seamlessly without

00:02:27.176 --> 00:02:29.706 A:middle
needed to learn or figure it

00:02:30.866 --> 00:02:30.946 A:middle
out.

00:02:31.216 --> 00:02:32.716 A:middle
So intent is the kind of thing

00:02:32.716 --> 00:02:34.786 A:middle
is hard to define but you know

00:02:34.786 --> 00:02:35.496 A:middle
it when you see it.

00:02:36.276 --> 00:02:37.356 A:middle
So I'm going to show you some

00:02:37.356 --> 00:02:39.746 A:middle
examples of apps that I found in

00:02:39.746 --> 00:02:41.876 A:middle
the last year that really

00:02:41.876 --> 00:02:44.026 A:middle
deliver real value to people and

00:02:44.026 --> 00:02:45.166 A:middle
really connect with them.

00:02:46.296 --> 00:02:48.236 A:middle
And I'm going to talk about five

00:02:48.236 --> 00:02:50.296 A:middle
elements of intentional design

00:02:50.296 --> 00:02:51.246 A:middle
that we can learn from these

00:02:51.246 --> 00:02:52.736 A:middle
apps and that you can apply to

00:02:52.736 --> 00:02:53.146 A:middle
your work.

00:02:54.196 --> 00:02:56.766 A:middle
So let's dive in.

00:02:57.926 --> 00:02:59.876 A:middle
So before mobile devices came

00:02:59.936 --> 00:03:01.516 A:middle
around when you traveled abroad

00:02:59.936 --> 00:03:01.516 A:middle
around when you traveled abroad

00:03:01.616 --> 00:03:02.706 A:middle
you'd carry a paper map.

00:03:03.816 --> 00:03:05.566 A:middle
And the advantage of the paper

00:03:05.566 --> 00:03:06.836 A:middle
map is that when you would

00:03:06.836 --> 00:03:08.736 A:middle
approach a local they would

00:03:08.736 --> 00:03:10.916 A:middle
instantly recognize what kind of

00:03:10.916 --> 00:03:11.826 A:middle
help you needed.

00:03:13.196 --> 00:03:15.306 A:middle
So mobile maps have made people

00:03:15.306 --> 00:03:16.826 A:middle
more independent, right?

00:03:16.826 --> 00:03:18.816 A:middle
We probably approach fewer

00:03:18.816 --> 00:03:20.466 A:middle
locals when we're traveling

00:03:20.466 --> 00:03:20.936 A:middle
abroad.

00:03:22.636 --> 00:03:24.136 A:middle
But in the same way that a paper

00:03:24.136 --> 00:03:26.646 A:middle
map invites an interaction,

00:03:26.906 --> 00:03:28.586 A:middle
there's an app called iTranslate

00:03:28.586 --> 00:03:30.336 A:middle
Converse that makes it easy to

00:03:30.336 --> 00:03:32.036 A:middle
approach a local with your

00:03:32.036 --> 00:03:33.766 A:middle
iPhone in your hand to ask a

00:03:33.766 --> 00:03:35.596 A:middle
question or get directions.

00:03:36.016 --> 00:03:37.486 A:middle
Some of you may have seen this

00:03:37.486 --> 00:03:39.126 A:middle
on Monday night at the Apple

00:03:39.126 --> 00:03:40.126 A:middle
Design Awards.

00:03:40.406 --> 00:03:42.666 A:middle
I'm going to go through a demo

00:03:42.666 --> 00:03:44.216 A:middle
to really bring out what I think

00:03:44.416 --> 00:03:46.056 A:middle
is really intentional about this

00:03:46.056 --> 00:03:46.316 A:middle
app.

00:03:47.016 --> 00:03:48.786 A:middle
So first of all there's very

00:03:48.786 --> 00:03:49.386 A:middle
little UI.

00:03:50.026 --> 00:03:51.736 A:middle
The screen is essentially one

00:03:51.736 --> 00:03:51.976 A:middle
big button.

00:03:52.106 --> 00:03:55.046 A:middle
I tap and hold and start

00:03:55.046 --> 00:03:55.536 A:middle
talking.

00:03:55.656 --> 00:03:56.416 A:middle
So I'll show you that in a

00:03:56.416 --> 00:03:56.896 A:middle
second.

00:03:57.416 --> 00:04:00.506 A:middle
And to be clear the goal of

00:03:57.416 --> 00:04:00.506 A:middle
And to be clear the goal of

00:04:00.596 --> 00:04:02.336 A:middle
iTranslate Converse is to make

00:04:02.336 --> 00:04:03.516 A:middle
conversation easy.

00:04:03.996 --> 00:04:05.596 A:middle
The developers have intended

00:04:05.596 --> 00:04:07.966 A:middle
this app to be used together.

00:04:08.176 --> 00:04:09.586 A:middle
So two people together, one of

00:04:09.586 --> 00:04:11.926 A:middle
whom most likely has never used

00:04:11.926 --> 00:04:13.686 A:middle
this app before, probably never

00:04:13.686 --> 00:04:15.676 A:middle
even seen it.

00:04:15.936 --> 00:04:18.736 A:middle
So I launched this app really

00:04:18.736 --> 00:04:20.696 A:middle
for real in in the Naples train

00:04:20.696 --> 00:04:23.106 A:middle
station when I was trying to get

00:04:23.106 --> 00:04:25.276 A:middle
on an express train to Rome and

00:04:25.276 --> 00:04:26.216 A:middle
the platforms were really

00:04:26.216 --> 00:04:26.996 A:middle
confusing.

00:04:27.386 --> 00:04:29.226 A:middle
So I pulled out my phone, I

00:04:29.226 --> 00:04:30.546 A:middle
launched the app, and I walked

00:04:30.546 --> 00:04:31.926 A:middle
up to a conductor.

00:04:32.516 --> 00:04:34.816 A:middle
So I said is this the express

00:04:34.856 --> 00:04:35.776 A:middle
train to Rome?

00:04:37.516 --> 00:04:39.926 A:middle
[Computerized Speaking Italian]

00:04:40.426 --> 00:04:42.076 A:middle
&gt;&gt; The app translated it into

00:04:42.076 --> 00:04:44.996 A:middle
Italian and the conductor heard.

00:04:46.346 --> 00:04:47.956 A:middle
Then I could flip the phone

00:04:48.226 --> 00:04:50.786 A:middle
around and again, what I find

00:04:50.856 --> 00:04:53.136 A:middle
interesting in this situation

00:04:53.236 --> 00:04:55.236 A:middle
that other person has probably

00:04:55.236 --> 00:04:56.586 A:middle
never seen this app before.

00:04:57.146 --> 00:05:00.856 A:middle
And they speak in a language

00:04:57.146 --> 00:05:00.856 A:middle
And they speak in a language

00:05:00.906 --> 00:05:02.376 A:middle
that I didn't speak but the app

00:05:02.376 --> 00:05:04.056 A:middle
is smart enough to know that

00:05:04.056 --> 00:05:05.466 A:middle
it's ether going to English or

00:05:05.466 --> 00:05:07.396 A:middle
Italian to listen for.

00:05:08.156 --> 00:05:10.336 A:middle
So the conductor spoke into the

00:05:10.336 --> 00:05:11.036 A:middle
microphone.

00:05:12.436 --> 00:05:13.666 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Platform Nine.

00:05:13.736 --> 00:05:16.226 A:middle
&gt;&gt; And the app translates it for

00:05:16.226 --> 00:05:16.356 A:middle
me.

00:05:16.786 --> 00:05:20.346 A:middle
So in reality he spoke English.

00:05:21.516 --> 00:05:23.516 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:05:24.516 --> 00:05:26.856 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:05:27.356 --> 00:05:29.166 A:middle
But he did want to see how the

00:05:29.166 --> 00:05:31.206 A:middle
app worked and I showed him and

00:05:31.206 --> 00:05:31.916 A:middle
he was impressed.

00:05:32.276 --> 00:05:35.876 A:middle
I think the real beauty of this

00:05:36.096 --> 00:05:37.496 A:middle
is that you can make a

00:05:37.496 --> 00:05:39.566 A:middle
connection with a person, right?

00:05:39.626 --> 00:05:41.816 A:middle
You can get on the right train

00:05:41.946 --> 00:05:44.076 A:middle
like I did, but you also make a

00:05:44.076 --> 00:05:45.996 A:middle
human connection in the process.

00:05:46.576 --> 00:05:50.006 A:middle
So the developer's intent here

00:05:50.006 --> 00:05:51.666 A:middle
is to enable communication

00:05:51.666 --> 00:05:53.506 A:middle
between two people in real time.

00:05:53.506 --> 00:05:55.586 A:middle
Just touch the screen and talk.

00:05:56.116 --> 00:05:57.456 A:middle
So the first element of

00:05:57.456 --> 00:05:59.796 A:middle
intentional design is what I'm

00:05:59.796 --> 00:06:00.986 A:middle
going to call radical

00:05:59.796 --> 00:06:00.986 A:middle
going to call radical

00:06:00.986 --> 00:06:02.016 A:middle
simplification.

00:06:03.346 --> 00:06:04.646 A:middle
So how did they do this?

00:06:05.956 --> 00:06:07.366 A:middle
Well, I think they considered

00:06:07.366 --> 00:06:09.286 A:middle
the context really well, the

00:06:09.286 --> 00:06:11.226 A:middle
context that this will be used

00:06:11.226 --> 00:06:11.546 A:middle
in.

00:06:12.246 --> 00:06:14.086 A:middle
They took into account where and

00:06:14.086 --> 00:06:15.696 A:middle
when people would pull out their

00:06:15.696 --> 00:06:18.326 A:middle
phone and launch their app.

00:06:18.846 --> 00:06:19.826 A:middle
You're probably in a foreign

00:06:19.826 --> 00:06:23.976 A:middle
country, like this guy you're

00:06:23.976 --> 00:06:27.936 A:middle
jetlagged, lost, tired, your

00:06:27.936 --> 00:06:31.256 A:middle
hair is uncombed, your jacket is

00:06:31.256 --> 00:06:31.856 A:middle
rumpled.

00:06:33.036 --> 00:06:35.106 A:middle
I'm not even sure if that's a

00:06:35.106 --> 00:06:37.156 A:middle
map that he's carrying at this

00:06:37.156 --> 00:06:38.466 A:middle
moment, it kind of looks like a

00:06:38.466 --> 00:06:38.876 A:middle
book.

00:06:40.046 --> 00:06:41.766 A:middle
So they remove the UI and allow

00:06:41.766 --> 00:06:42.996 A:middle
people to focus on what they

00:06:42.996 --> 00:06:44.416 A:middle
need, which is to find

00:06:44.416 --> 00:06:47.336 A:middle
something, to ask a question, to

00:06:47.336 --> 00:06:48.056 A:middle
get their bearings.

00:06:48.946 --> 00:06:52.936 A:middle
And it's amazing how much an

00:06:52.936 --> 00:06:54.866 A:middle
experience can change when

00:06:54.866 --> 00:06:56.756 A:middle
actions are removed from the UI.

00:06:56.756 --> 00:06:58.986 A:middle
So I want to show you another

00:06:58.986 --> 00:06:59.656 A:middle
example.

00:07:00.416 --> 00:07:02.056 A:middle
This is an app called Vanido.

00:07:02.476 --> 00:07:03.876 A:middle
It helps you learn how to sing.

00:07:05.116 --> 00:07:06.626 A:middle
So if you're the kind of person

00:07:06.856 --> 00:07:08.366 A:middle
who wants to learn how to sing

00:07:08.956 --> 00:07:11.426 A:middle
with literally no one hearing

00:07:11.426 --> 00:07:13.696 A:middle
your or judging you, this app is

00:07:13.696 --> 00:07:14.246 A:middle
amazing.

00:07:15.196 --> 00:07:16.336 A:middle
This is the UI.

00:07:17.166 --> 00:07:18.396 A:middle
It's so simple.

00:07:19.066 --> 00:07:20.576 A:middle
The app tracks the pitch of my

00:07:20.576 --> 00:07:22.836 A:middle
voice while I'm singing and it's

00:07:22.836 --> 00:07:24.596 A:middle
continually giving me feedback.

00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:26.606 A:middle
Am I hitting my notes or not?

00:07:27.876 --> 00:07:28.906 A:middle
So let me show you.

00:07:29.516 --> 00:07:33.056 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:07:33.556 --> 00:07:35.066 A:middle
I'm actually not going to do a

00:07:35.066 --> 00:07:35.706 A:middle
live demo.

00:07:36.241 --> 00:07:38.241 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:07:38.466 --> 00:07:39.836 A:middle
But I am going to sing along

00:07:40.301 --> 00:07:42.301 A:middle
[harmonica note]

00:07:42.586 --> 00:07:45.536 A:middle
because I've been practicing and

00:07:45.536 --> 00:07:48.476 A:middle
I want you to see how it works.

00:07:50.516 --> 00:07:57.516 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:07:58.516 --> 00:08:06.126 A:middle
[ Cheering ]

00:07:58.516 --> 00:08:06.126 A:middle
[ Cheering ]

00:08:06.626 --> 00:08:08.856 A:middle
You can leave feedback in my

00:08:09.086 --> 00:08:09.526 A:middle
session.

00:08:10.131 --> 00:08:12.131 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:08:12.246 --> 00:08:14.076 A:middle
So what I love about Vanido is

00:08:14.116 --> 00:08:16.376 A:middle
that it has stripped away what

00:08:16.376 --> 00:08:18.606 A:middle
music education looks like,

00:08:18.606 --> 00:08:18.846 A:middle
right?

00:08:18.846 --> 00:08:20.326 A:middle
There's no charts or notes.

00:08:20.396 --> 00:08:22.666 A:middle
It's colorful, it's animated,

00:08:22.666 --> 00:08:23.496 A:middle
and it's fun.

00:08:24.376 --> 00:08:25.766 A:middle
And you should have heard me

00:08:25.766 --> 00:08:27.866 A:middle
sing before I started using this

00:08:27.866 --> 00:08:28.086 A:middle
app.

00:08:28.416 --> 00:08:29.356 A:middle
It really works.

00:08:29.786 --> 00:08:31.806 A:middle
And there's only one interactive

00:08:31.806 --> 00:08:33.046 A:middle
element on the screen when

00:08:33.046 --> 00:08:34.256 A:middle
you're singing and it's way up

00:08:34.256 --> 00:08:35.826 A:middle
at the top left.

00:08:36.676 --> 00:08:38.506 A:middle
So you can hold your phone like

00:08:38.506 --> 00:08:40.336 A:middle
a microphone and really belt it

00:08:40.336 --> 00:08:42.666 A:middle
out without worrying about

00:08:42.666 --> 00:08:44.096 A:middle
accidentally exiting your

00:08:44.096 --> 00:08:44.576 A:middle
lesson.

00:08:47.066 --> 00:08:47.756 A:middle
So this is radical

00:08:47.756 --> 00:08:49.656 A:middle
simplification and that's what I

00:08:49.656 --> 00:08:50.516 A:middle
mean, that's the first

00:08:50.516 --> 00:08:52.736 A:middle
manifestation of intent and

00:08:52.836 --> 00:08:54.116 A:middle
intentional design.

00:08:55.656 --> 00:08:57.396 A:middle
Being radical means taking

00:08:57.396 --> 00:08:58.906 A:middle
risks, right?

00:08:58.906 --> 00:09:00.266 A:middle
Removing a bunch of stuff from

00:08:58.906 --> 00:09:00.266 A:middle
Removing a bunch of stuff from

00:09:00.266 --> 00:09:02.116 A:middle
the UI could be jarring if you

00:09:02.116 --> 00:09:02.906 A:middle
don't do it right.

00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:04.286 A:middle
But I think there's a way to

00:09:04.286 --> 00:09:05.276 A:middle
reduce your risk.

00:09:05.486 --> 00:09:07.356 A:middle
So next I want to talk about

00:09:07.356 --> 00:09:09.786 A:middle
people and about orienting your

00:09:09.786 --> 00:09:12.306 A:middle
design around what people really

00:09:12.306 --> 00:09:12.716 A:middle
want.

00:09:13.206 --> 00:09:14.426 A:middle
So what do they want?

00:09:14.876 --> 00:09:16.466 A:middle
I think this is worth exploring

00:09:16.816 --> 00:09:17.756 A:middle
because it's almost never

00:09:17.756 --> 00:09:18.426 A:middle
obvious.

00:09:20.036 --> 00:09:22.536 A:middle
The first needs that you see

00:09:22.536 --> 00:09:24.156 A:middle
when you start kind of looking

00:09:24.286 --> 00:09:27.206 A:middle
at people and the users that you

00:09:27.206 --> 00:09:28.806 A:middle
might want to serve are

00:09:28.806 --> 00:09:30.476 A:middle
superficial and you need to dig

00:09:30.476 --> 00:09:31.436 A:middle
past those.

00:09:31.986 --> 00:09:33.206 A:middle
They might be the first ones

00:09:33.206 --> 00:09:34.616 A:middle
that you think about addressing

00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:35.776 A:middle
or they might be the ones that

00:09:35.776 --> 00:09:37.406 A:middle
pulled you into the problem in

00:09:37.406 --> 00:09:39.876 A:middle
the first place, but you need to

00:09:39.876 --> 00:09:42.516 A:middle
keep digging because those

00:09:42.616 --> 00:09:45.096 A:middle
superficial needs often mask

00:09:45.556 --> 00:09:46.946 A:middle
deeper needs, right, you could

00:09:46.946 --> 00:09:48.646 A:middle
solve them but not really solve

00:09:48.646 --> 00:09:50.396 A:middle
the persons' problem.

00:09:50.676 --> 00:09:52.556 A:middle
So you have to keep digging.

00:09:53.146 --> 00:09:54.516 A:middle
The second element of

00:09:54.516 --> 00:09:55.786 A:middle
intentional design that I want

00:09:55.786 --> 00:09:57.546 A:middle
to get into here is called deep

00:09:57.546 --> 00:09:58.506 A:middle
understanding.

00:09:58.666 --> 00:10:00.046 A:middle
So knowing the person that you

00:09:58.666 --> 00:10:00.046 A:middle
So knowing the person that you

00:10:00.046 --> 00:10:01.706 A:middle
want to reach and the actually

00:10:01.706 --> 00:10:02.796 A:middle
problem that they have.

00:10:03.556 --> 00:10:05.726 A:middle
The deeper you dig the more

00:10:05.726 --> 00:10:07.386 A:middle
likely you are to see where the

00:10:07.486 --> 00:10:09.616 A:middle
real opportunity to meet their

00:10:09.616 --> 00:10:10.406 A:middle
needs is.

00:10:10.696 --> 00:10:12.196 A:middle
And the app that really shows

00:10:12.196 --> 00:10:14.066 A:middle
this off, in my opinion, is

00:10:14.066 --> 00:10:15.296 A:middle
called Streaks Workout.

00:10:16.216 --> 00:10:17.916 A:middle
So it's a workout app but I want

00:10:17.916 --> 00:10:19.076 A:middle
to go behind the scenes a little

00:10:19.076 --> 00:10:19.306 A:middle
bit.

00:10:20.016 --> 00:10:22.176 A:middle
On the surface it looks like

00:10:22.176 --> 00:10:23.266 A:middle
many workout apps.

00:10:23.266 --> 00:10:24.536 A:middle
It guides your workouts.

00:10:24.626 --> 00:10:26.456 A:middle
This is the primary screen and

00:10:26.456 --> 00:10:27.426 A:middle
it looks pretty simple.

00:10:27.646 --> 00:10:29.536 A:middle
You pick a workout duration and

00:10:29.536 --> 00:10:29.976 A:middle
you go.

00:10:30.566 --> 00:10:34.716 A:middle
But personally, I'll confess

00:10:34.776 --> 00:10:36.466 A:middle
that I don't love working out

00:10:37.516 --> 00:10:40.826 A:middle
and I've tried many workout apps

00:10:40.826 --> 00:10:43.566 A:middle
that I just don't stick with and

00:10:43.566 --> 00:10:46.506 A:middle
I want to thank any developers

00:10:46.506 --> 00:10:47.776 A:middle
that are here who have developed

00:10:47.776 --> 00:10:49.456 A:middle
workout apps that I've tried

00:10:49.646 --> 00:10:51.356 A:middle
because I respect your effort

00:10:51.966 --> 00:10:55.376 A:middle
and I'm really trying to get fit

00:10:55.376 --> 00:10:56.476 A:middle
so thank you for that.

00:10:56.866 --> 00:10:58.106 A:middle
But what I struggle with is

00:10:58.106 --> 00:11:00.046 A:middle
staying motivated.

00:10:58.106 --> 00:11:00.046 A:middle
staying motivated.

