in the way of our ability to

00:28:17.926 --> 00:28:19.566 A:middle
reckon with new problems.

00:28:19.706 --> 00:28:20.726 A:middle
Sometimes we won't even

00:28:20.726 --> 00:28:22.226 A:middle
recognize that the problems are

00:28:22.226 --> 00:28:24.626 A:middle
new and this is true of anyone

00:28:24.686 --> 00:28:26.636 A:middle
who has tried to make anything

00:28:26.636 --> 00:28:28.886 A:middle
new ever, right?

00:28:29.156 --> 00:28:31.146 A:middle
Suitcases once had a form.

00:28:31.586 --> 00:28:33.266 A:middle
They were rectangular and the

00:28:33.266 --> 00:28:34.726 A:middle
long side was down.

00:28:35.796 --> 00:28:37.966 A:middle
That form was adjusted but the

00:28:37.966 --> 00:28:39.546 A:middle
fundamental elements were always

00:28:39.546 --> 00:28:40.536 A:middle
taken as a given.

00:28:40.976 --> 00:28:43.426 A:middle
The wheels were tacked on but

00:28:43.426 --> 00:28:45.476 A:middle
the overall form stayed the

00:28:45.476 --> 00:28:45.966 A:middle
same.

00:28:46.716 --> 00:28:49.826 A:middle
For decades smart people

00:28:50.246 --> 00:28:52.306 A:middle
considered this form and stopped

00:28:52.306 --> 00:28:52.696 A:middle
there.

00:28:53.186 --> 00:28:55.246 A:middle
It took someone with a very

00:28:55.246 --> 00:28:57.646 A:middle
sharp focus on an extreme

00:28:57.646 --> 00:29:00.006 A:middle
audience to break out of this

00:28:57.646 --> 00:29:00.006 A:middle
audience to break out of this

00:29:00.006 --> 00:29:03.446 A:middle
pattern, right, and turn the

00:29:03.446 --> 00:29:04.726 A:middle
form on it's head [laughing].

00:29:06.636 --> 00:29:06.976 A:middle
Thank you.

00:29:07.516 --> 00:29:09.546 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:29:10.046 --> 00:29:12.136 A:middle
So we apply patterns

00:29:12.136 --> 00:29:12.906 A:middle
automatically.

00:29:13.586 --> 00:29:15.486 A:middle
Our brains make connections

00:29:15.486 --> 00:29:17.306 A:middle
quickly and that has benefits,

00:29:17.306 --> 00:29:17.506 A:middle
right?

00:29:17.506 --> 00:29:18.996 A:middle
It helps us work efficiently.

00:29:19.606 --> 00:29:21.956 A:middle
It helps us be consistent, but

00:29:21.956 --> 00:29:23.206 A:middle
it also prevents us from

00:29:23.206 --> 00:29:25.506 A:middle
noticing the obvious and

00:29:25.506 --> 00:29:27.766 A:middle
challenging it, asking

00:29:27.766 --> 00:29:29.106 A:middle
fundamental questions, why does

00:29:29.146 --> 00:29:31.026 A:middle
this thing need to be this way?

00:29:31.426 --> 00:29:33.786 A:middle
So as a UI designer it's really

00:29:33.786 --> 00:29:36.356 A:middle
tempting always to draw on

00:29:36.426 --> 00:29:38.336 A:middle
familiar UI elements to solve

00:29:38.336 --> 00:29:39.216 A:middle
new problems.

00:29:39.826 --> 00:29:41.786 A:middle
I'm sure you're familiar with

00:29:41.786 --> 00:29:42.906 A:middle
the house icon.

00:29:43.306 --> 00:29:44.926 A:middle
It made sense in a desktop

00:29:44.926 --> 00:29:45.476 A:middle
browser.

00:29:45.916 --> 00:29:48.766 A:middle
A browser is a frame for the

00:29:48.896 --> 00:29:50.026 A:middle
Internet universe.

00:29:50.576 --> 00:29:52.956 A:middle
A browser home button will lift

00:29:52.956 --> 00:29:55.456 A:middle
you out of whatever corner of

00:29:55.456 --> 00:29:57.776 A:middle
the dark web that you found

00:29:57.776 --> 00:30:00.036 A:middle
yourself in and allows you to

00:29:57.776 --> 00:30:00.036 A:middle
yourself in and allows you to

00:30:00.036 --> 00:30:00.976 A:middle
get out of there.

00:30:01.816 --> 00:30:02.896 A:middle
So that notion of home was

00:30:02.896 --> 00:30:04.336 A:middle
extended to iPhone and the

00:30:04.336 --> 00:30:05.756 A:middle
behavior is similar.

00:30:06.886 --> 00:30:08.776 A:middle
It's a shortcut, it's an easy

00:30:08.776 --> 00:30:10.406 A:middle
button, home is a starting

00:30:10.406 --> 00:30:13.556 A:middle
place, and unlike in real life,

00:30:13.556 --> 00:30:14.926 A:middle
home is a place that you can

00:30:14.926 --> 00:30:17.056 A:middle
always return to with a simple

00:30:17.056 --> 00:30:17.636 A:middle
gesture.

00:30:18.436 --> 00:30:20.646 A:middle
You can go home whenever you

00:30:20.646 --> 00:30:21.016 A:middle
want.

00:30:22.636 --> 00:30:24.326 A:middle
So home is also a familiar

00:30:24.326 --> 00:30:25.416 A:middle
notion in the finder.

00:30:25.416 --> 00:30:27.206 A:middle
Here the spirit is more like --

00:30:28.306 --> 00:30:30.556 A:middle
you followed the river to it's

00:30:30.556 --> 00:30:31.396 A:middle
headwaters.

00:30:32.346 --> 00:30:33.756 A:middle
On the Mac, home represents a

00:30:33.756 --> 00:30:34.526 A:middle
container.

00:30:34.846 --> 00:30:36.046 A:middle
Everything is in here.

00:30:36.486 --> 00:30:37.686 A:middle
You don't need to look anywhere

00:30:37.686 --> 00:30:37.986 A:middle
else.

00:30:38.446 --> 00:30:40.866 A:middle
you have reached the source.

00:30:42.736 --> 00:30:45.406 A:middle
Home in these contexts offers

00:30:45.496 --> 00:30:48.236 A:middle
reliability, safety, an ability

00:30:48.236 --> 00:30:50.066 A:middle
to return as you navigate

00:30:50.066 --> 00:30:50.616 A:middle
outward.

00:30:51.076 --> 00:30:54.256 A:middle
And it's clear obvious utility

00:30:54.466 --> 00:30:56.926 A:middle
elsewhere on the platform might

00:30:56.926 --> 00:30:58.716 A:middle
seem like a reasonable choice as

00:30:58.716 --> 00:31:00.466 A:middle
a tab bar icon, right?

00:30:58.716 --> 00:31:00.466 A:middle
a tab bar icon, right?

00:31:03.296 --> 00:31:04.866 A:middle
Except there's a crucial

00:31:04.866 --> 00:31:06.456 A:middle
difference in using the notion

00:31:06.456 --> 00:31:07.726 A:middle
of home in a tab bar.

00:31:08.976 --> 00:31:12.226 A:middle
To be blunt, an app isn't a

00:31:12.226 --> 00:31:14.656 A:middle
frame containing god knows what.

00:31:15.686 --> 00:31:18.216 A:middle
A typical app offers specific

00:31:18.216 --> 00:31:20.026 A:middle
things, specific contents,

00:31:20.026 --> 00:31:21.746 A:middle
specific tools, specific

00:31:21.746 --> 00:31:22.426 A:middle
actions.

00:31:22.746 --> 00:31:24.826 A:middle
And a tab bar is a quick

00:31:24.826 --> 00:31:26.726 A:middle
expression of the overall

00:31:26.726 --> 00:31:28.246 A:middle
utility of your app.

00:31:28.246 --> 00:31:30.066 A:middle
It's a high-level map of your

00:31:31.366 --> 00:31:31.433 A:middle
app.

00:31:31.696 --> 00:31:33.676 A:middle
So let's use an example that's

00:31:33.676 --> 00:31:36.016 A:middle
close to home -- the tab bar of

00:31:36.016 --> 00:31:37.866 A:middle
WWDC app.

00:31:38.796 --> 00:31:41.486 A:middle
So we all can get a quick

00:31:41.486 --> 00:31:43.946 A:middle
understanding of the scope of

00:31:43.946 --> 00:31:45.596 A:middle
information that's available in

00:31:45.596 --> 00:31:47.226 A:middle
the app simply by scanning the

00:31:47.226 --> 00:31:47.786 A:middle
tab bar.

00:31:48.846 --> 00:31:50.196 A:middle
We can guess at what content

00:31:50.196 --> 00:31:52.716 A:middle
might be in each tab.

00:31:52.716 --> 00:31:54.756 A:middle
So tab bar icons and tab bar

00:31:54.756 --> 00:31:56.556 A:middle
labels should be as direct as

00:31:56.556 --> 00:31:57.246 A:middle
possible.

00:31:57.976 --> 00:32:00.086 A:middle
And this directness will then

00:31:57.976 --> 00:32:00.086 A:middle
And this directness will then

00:32:00.086 --> 00:32:02.896 A:middle
limit what each tab can contain

00:32:02.896 --> 00:32:03.766 A:middle
and that's great.

00:32:04.976 --> 00:32:06.296 A:middle
Directness creates

00:32:06.296 --> 00:32:07.246 A:middle
predictability.

00:32:07.736 --> 00:32:09.166 A:middle
So the app may not do

00:32:09.166 --> 00:32:12.836 A:middle
everything, right, no app does

00:32:12.836 --> 00:32:13.346 A:middle
everything.

00:32:14.036 --> 00:32:15.166 A:middle
But people won't have to hunt

00:32:15.166 --> 00:32:16.466 A:middle
around to figure out what it

00:32:16.466 --> 00:32:17.656 A:middle
does and doesn't do.

00:32:18.916 --> 00:32:20.726 A:middle
So when I talk about home I'm

00:32:20.726 --> 00:32:21.816 A:middle
talking about a metaphor,

00:32:22.856 --> 00:32:24.816 A:middle
homeland, a home base.

00:32:27.056 --> 00:32:29.186 A:middle
So let's just dig in to why home

00:32:29.256 --> 00:32:29.946 A:middle
doesn't work.

00:32:30.306 --> 00:32:32.506 A:middle
First it's overly broad and it

00:32:32.506 --> 00:32:33.516 A:middle
feels generic.

00:32:34.686 --> 00:32:36.126 A:middle
And I think it's a copout.

00:32:36.556 --> 00:32:37.996 A:middle
You're avoiding a decision by

00:32:37.996 --> 00:32:39.246 A:middle
naming a tab Home.

00:32:39.896 --> 00:32:41.876 A:middle
The perceived comforts of home

00:32:41.876 --> 00:32:44.236 A:middle
as an icon in a label are

00:32:44.236 --> 00:32:45.406 A:middle
getting in the way of being

00:32:45.406 --> 00:32:47.596 A:middle
direct, of clearly and directly

00:32:47.596 --> 00:32:48.976 A:middle
communicating the scope of

00:32:48.976 --> 00:32:50.616 A:middle
what's in your app.

00:32:50.846 --> 00:32:53.236 A:middle
If your app is a meditation app

00:32:53.776 --> 00:32:55.796 A:middle
and offers content related to

00:32:55.856 --> 00:32:57.046 A:middle
meditating and building a

00:32:57.046 --> 00:33:01.036 A:middle
meditation practice, imagine the

00:32:57.046 --> 00:33:01.036 A:middle
meditation practice, imagine the

00:33:01.036 --> 00:33:02.666 A:middle
impression that it would leave

00:33:02.666 --> 00:33:04.686 A:middle
on people if not only the tab

00:33:04.686 --> 00:33:06.456 A:middle
bar was more direct, but the

00:33:06.456 --> 00:33:07.976 A:middle
directness of the tab bar

00:33:08.276 --> 00:33:10.256 A:middle
enforced a simplicity and an

00:33:10.326 --> 00:33:12.296 A:middle
order on the content that you

00:33:12.296 --> 00:33:12.926 A:middle
display.

00:33:13.006 --> 00:33:15.576 A:middle
And that content was predictable

00:33:15.746 --> 00:33:17.356 A:middle
and directly organized.

00:33:18.586 --> 00:33:20.236 A:middle
So indirect labels feel

00:33:20.236 --> 00:33:22.246 A:middle
conventional and they feel safe

00:33:22.356 --> 00:33:23.726 A:middle
but they mask utility.

00:33:24.406 --> 00:33:25.786 A:middle
Like a storage locker you're

00:33:25.786 --> 00:33:27.066 A:middle
putting your valuable stuff

00:33:27.196 --> 00:33:29.066 A:middle
behind a door that's anonymous

00:33:29.096 --> 00:33:29.946 A:middle
and inscrutable.

00:33:30.246 --> 00:33:32.176 A:middle
And this is what I mean by

00:33:32.176 --> 00:33:33.396 A:middle
unintentional design.

00:33:34.666 --> 00:33:36.436 A:middle
No one intends to be indirect.

00:33:38.216 --> 00:33:40.516 A:middle
Being intentional will lead to

00:33:40.556 --> 00:33:41.886 A:middle
cleaner and clearer

00:33:41.886 --> 00:33:42.706 A:middle
communication.

00:33:42.706 --> 00:33:44.846 A:middle
And this brings me to my final

00:33:44.846 --> 00:33:45.936 A:middle
element of intent.

00:33:46.466 --> 00:33:47.976 A:middle
Direct communication.

00:33:48.216 --> 00:33:49.806 A:middle
Intentionally design things.

00:33:49.916 --> 00:33:51.366 A:middle
Clearly communicate to the

00:33:51.366 --> 00:33:52.466 A:middle
people who use them.

00:33:52.836 --> 00:33:55.766 A:middle
And the way to achieve this is

00:33:55.766 --> 00:33:57.486 A:middle
to draw on what people learn on

00:33:57.486 --> 00:33:59.606 A:middle
the platform and in the world.

00:34:00.156 --> 00:34:01.456 A:middle
So I want to show you a couple

00:34:01.496 --> 00:34:04.266 A:middle
of last quick examples of apps

00:34:04.356 --> 00:34:06.616 A:middle
that rely on a familiar form to

00:34:06.616 --> 00:34:08.356 A:middle
make interactions feel useful.

00:34:09.976 --> 00:34:12.065 A:middle
So the core concept of an app

00:34:12.065 --> 00:34:13.666 A:middle
called Tinycards is to bring

00:34:13.666 --> 00:34:15.045 A:middle
flashcards on to a mobile

00:34:15.045 --> 00:34:15.636 A:middle
advice.

00:34:15.856 --> 00:34:17.416 A:middle
You can use them to memorize

00:34:17.525 --> 00:34:18.315 A:middle
pretty much anything --

00:34:18.315 --> 00:34:20.916 A:middle
languages, flowers, leaves,

00:34:21.505 --> 00:34:22.306 A:middle
almost anything.

00:34:22.835 --> 00:34:25.255 A:middle
So the interaction within the

00:34:25.255 --> 00:34:26.516 A:middle
app is super direct.

00:34:26.676 --> 00:34:28.226 A:middle
People expect cards to have

00:34:28.226 --> 00:34:29.916 A:middle
dimension, so that periodic

00:34:29.916 --> 00:34:31.686 A:middle
pulse is inviting you to

00:34:31.686 --> 00:34:32.866 A:middle
interact with the card.

00:34:33.815 --> 00:34:35.156 A:middle
You flip the card over by

00:34:35.156 --> 00:34:35.735 A:middle
tapping it.

00:34:36.085 --> 00:34:37.716 A:middle
So these cards have two sides.

00:34:38.856 --> 00:34:40.286 A:middle
They've respected the metaphor

00:34:40.286 --> 00:34:41.005 A:middle
of the card.

00:34:42.116 --> 00:34:43.416 A:middle
People appreciate that.

00:34:43.916 --> 00:34:47.525 A:middle
So the entire experience of

00:34:47.585 --> 00:34:49.516 A:middle
Tinycards is based on quickly

00:34:49.516 --> 00:34:51.076 A:middle
flicking through these cards as

00:34:51.076 --> 00:34:52.386 A:middle
you commit things to memory.

00:34:52.795 --> 00:34:54.775 A:middle
Like for instance the flags of

00:34:54.775 --> 00:34:55.906 A:middle
Canadian provinces.

00:34:55.906 --> 00:34:56.926 A:middle
Does anyone know this one?

00:35:00.116 --> 00:35:01.886 A:middle
Ontario. Let's try it.

00:35:04.556 --> 00:35:05.236 A:middle
Oh my gosh.

00:35:06.196 --> 00:35:07.796 A:middle
You've done that quiz before,

00:35:08.466 --> 00:35:08.566 A:middle
right?

00:35:09.856 --> 00:35:12.086 A:middle
So the UI of Tinycards is so

00:35:12.086 --> 00:35:13.876 A:middle
clear you don't even think about

00:35:13.876 --> 00:35:14.016 A:middle
it.

00:35:14.186 --> 00:35:15.666 A:middle
Working with cards feels

00:35:15.666 --> 00:35:17.056 A:middle
completely natural and you can

00:35:17.056 --> 00:35:18.386 A:middle
just focus on your goal, which

00:35:18.386 --> 00:35:19.266 A:middle
is learning stuff.

00:35:20.616 --> 00:35:22.466 A:middle
So what Tinycards demonstrates

00:35:22.466 --> 00:35:24.336 A:middle
to me is that if you implement a

00:35:24.336 --> 00:35:26.056 A:middle
metaphor well, people will

00:35:26.116 --> 00:35:27.266 A:middle
instantly become immersed.

00:35:27.266 --> 00:35:28.386 A:middle
They'll forget that they're even

00:35:28.386 --> 00:35:29.566 A:middle
interacting with a UI.

00:35:30.336 --> 00:35:33.026 A:middle
And once they're immersed, you

00:35:33.026 --> 00:35:34.876 A:middle
even have the opportunity to

00:35:34.876 --> 00:35:36.926 A:middle
extend the metaphor, to really

00:35:36.926 --> 00:35:38.776 A:middle
surprise and even delight

00:35:38.886 --> 00:35:39.246 A:middle
people.

00:35:40.066 --> 00:35:41.686 A:middle
So I want to show you a game.

00:35:42.166 --> 00:35:43.856 A:middle
It's called Gorogoa and it

00:35:43.856 --> 00:35:45.796 A:middle
extends the metaphor of the card

00:35:45.976 --> 00:35:47.536 A:middle
in a way that I feel like

00:35:47.576 --> 00:35:49.216 A:middle
creates a truly unique

00:35:49.216 --> 00:35:50.076 A:middle
experience.

00:35:50.856 --> 00:35:52.806 A:middle
So Gorogoa is a puzzle game.

00:35:53.266 --> 00:35:55.616 A:middle
You move cards around a grid and

00:35:55.616 --> 00:35:57.516 A:middle
you advance in the game and in

00:35:57.516 --> 00:35:58.986 A:middle
the story by getting them into

00:35:58.986 --> 00:36:00.086 A:middle
the right positions.

00:35:58.986 --> 00:36:00.086 A:middle
the right positions.

00:36:00.736 --> 00:36:01.866 A:middle
But you could see that these

00:36:01.866 --> 00:36:03.976 A:middle
cards do things that no actual

00:36:03.976 --> 00:36:05.026 A:middle
cards can do.

00:36:05.386 --> 00:36:07.886 A:middle
They can be torn off and as

00:36:07.886 --> 00:36:09.026 A:middle
you'll see in a moment they can

00:36:09.026 --> 00:36:10.366 A:middle
actually stitch themselves

00:36:10.366 --> 00:36:12.756 A:middle
together into a scene.

00:36:18.116 --> 00:36:19.246 A:middle
Yeah, this is an incredible

00:36:19.246 --> 00:36:19.616 A:middle
game.

00:36:20.236 --> 00:36:22.236 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:36:22.456 --> 00:36:24.176 A:middle
And it's a great example of how

00:36:24.176 --> 00:36:25.596 A:middle
you can extend the metaphor

00:36:25.696 --> 00:36:27.386 A:middle
farther than you might think and

00:36:27.386 --> 00:36:29.206 A:middle
create something truly amazing.

00:36:29.686 --> 00:36:31.566 A:middle
This moment right here where

00:36:31.566 --> 00:36:32.976 A:middle
you've got this card metaphor

00:36:32.976 --> 00:36:34.396 A:middle
that suddenly kind of

00:36:34.396 --> 00:36:35.966 A:middle
disappears, that's purely

00:36:35.966 --> 00:36:37.906 A:middle
delightful and it's really I

00:36:37.976 --> 00:36:39.966 A:middle
think a great testament to how

00:36:39.966 --> 00:36:42.266 A:middle
well he's implemented the

00:36:42.266 --> 00:36:43.286 A:middle
metaphor of cards.

00:36:45.456 --> 00:36:47.476 A:middle
Bending and extending metaphors

00:36:47.476 --> 00:36:49.626 A:middle
doesn't work if the result

00:36:49.666 --> 00:36:51.666 A:middle
doesn't extend the utility, or

00:36:51.666 --> 00:36:53.556 A:middle
value, or delight of your app.

00:36:53.616 --> 00:36:55.806 A:middle
That's why the home tab on the

00:36:56.106 --> 00:36:57.556 A:middle
tab bar doesn't work, right?

00:36:57.556 --> 00:36:59.506 A:middle
It doesn't extend the utility of

00:36:59.506 --> 00:37:01.676 A:middle
the app or create any additional

00:36:59.506 --> 00:37:01.676 A:middle
the app or create any additional

00:37:01.676 --> 00:37:02.206 A:middle
value.

00:37:03.316 --> 00:37:05.046 A:middle
So the last app I want to show

00:37:05.046 --> 00:37:08.226 A:middle
you is an example that combines

00:37:08.226 --> 00:37:09.906 A:middle
metaphors from the real and

00:37:09.906 --> 00:37:11.466 A:middle
digital world in a really simple

00:37:11.466 --> 00:37:11.966 A:middle
way.

00:37:11.966 --> 00:37:13.426 A:middle
It's called Rosarium.

00:37:13.966 --> 00:37:14.056 A:middle
Yeah.

00:37:15.516 --> 00:37:19.546 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:37:20.046 --> 00:37:22.486 A:middle
I think the developers are here.

00:37:22.486 --> 00:37:23.746 A:middle
It's a rosary that you wear on

00:37:23.746 --> 00:37:25.526 A:middle
your wrist and I believe that is

00:37:25.526 --> 00:37:29.526 A:middle
Latin and the font is really

00:37:29.526 --> 00:37:30.816 A:middle
communicating to me that it's

00:37:30.816 --> 00:37:32.046 A:middle
Latin anyway.

00:37:32.226 --> 00:37:34.236 A:middle
So the beads are represented by

00:37:34.236 --> 00:37:34.876 A:middle
circles.

00:37:34.966 --> 00:37:36.416 A:middle
Each time you turn the digital

00:37:36.416 --> 00:37:38.516 A:middle
crown you get a slight haptic

00:37:38.576 --> 00:37:38.836 A:middle
tab.

00:37:39.406 --> 00:37:40.676 A:middle
So when I met the developers

00:37:40.676 --> 00:37:42.156 A:middle
they told me that they were

00:37:42.156 --> 00:37:44.086 A:middle
inspired by the similarity

00:37:44.086 --> 00:37:46.276 A:middle
between the feel of rotating the

00:37:46.276 --> 00:37:48.276 A:middle
digital crown and the feel of an

00:37:48.366 --> 00:37:49.566 A:middle
actual rosary bead.

00:37:49.976 --> 00:37:52.736 A:middle
So the app has translated this

00:37:52.736 --> 00:37:54.866 A:middle
real world object, just a strand

00:37:54.866 --> 00:37:56.616 A:middle
of beads, into the virtual world

00:37:56.616 --> 00:37:58.866 A:middle
in a way that feels really

00:37:58.866 --> 00:37:59.476 A:middle
natural.

00:38:00.696 --> 00:38:01.966 A:middle
So I'm no suggesting that it's a

00:38:01.966 --> 00:38:04.116 A:middle
replacement for rosary beads or

00:38:04.116 --> 00:38:05.546 A:middle
any prayer beads because the

00:38:05.546 --> 00:38:07.496 A:middle
physical beads can have deep,

00:38:07.716 --> 00:38:09.056 A:middle
you know, personal meaning.

00:38:09.576 --> 00:38:11.066 A:middle
But I love how they've

00:38:11.066 --> 00:38:13.066 A:middle
thoughtfully carried that real

00:38:13.066 --> 00:38:14.786 A:middle
world experience into a digital

00:38:14.786 --> 00:38:16.626 A:middle
form in a way that's so

00:38:16.626 --> 00:38:18.476 A:middle
radically simple and clear.

00:38:19.486 --> 00:38:20.666 A:middle
And I think it really

00:38:21.556 --> 00:38:23.516 A:middle
illustrates each of the points

00:38:23.516 --> 00:38:24.646 A:middle
that I made earlier -- the

00:38:24.646 --> 00:38:26.326 A:middle
simplicity and the understanding

00:38:26.326 --> 00:38:28.946 A:middle
of people, the extreme kind of

00:38:28.946 --> 00:38:31.256 A:middle
focus on a problem and the

00:38:31.256 --> 00:38:32.906 A:middle
direct communication of a

00:38:32.906 --> 00:38:33.626 A:middle
solution.

00:38:34.086 --> 00:38:36.736 A:middle
And this is intent in action.

00:38:36.736 --> 00:38:38.226 A:middle
This is being intentional in

00:38:38.226 --> 00:38:38.756 A:middle
design.

00:38:38.756 --> 00:38:41.036 A:middle
It's a matter of turning off the

00:38:41.036 --> 00:38:43.956 A:middle
automatic part of your brain, of

00:38:43.956 --> 00:38:46.176 A:middle
slowing down, and challenging

00:38:46.176 --> 00:38:46.956 A:middle
the obvious.

00:38:48.506 --> 00:38:51.216 A:middle
It requires a level of intention

00:38:51.386 --> 00:38:53.326 A:middle
that will enable your decisions

00:38:53.326 --> 00:38:55.266 A:middle
to become more conscious and for

00:38:55.266 --> 00:38:57.186 A:middle
you to become aware of the

00:38:57.186 --> 00:38:58.876 A:middle
patterns and the familiar things

00:38:58.876 --> 00:39:00.016 A:middle
that might get in the way and

00:38:58.876 --> 00:39:00.016 A:middle
that might get in the way and

00:39:00.016 --> 00:39:02.996 A:middle
block you and focus on people,

00:39:03.356 --> 00:39:03.566 A:middle
right?

00:39:03.566 --> 00:39:04.486 A:middle
The people that you want to

00:39:04.536 --> 00:39:06.706 A:middle
serve, the person who inspires

00:39:06.706 --> 00:39:08.446 A:middle
you, the family member who

00:39:08.446 --> 00:39:10.696 A:middle
allows you to be the best

00:39:10.806 --> 00:39:12.506 A:middle
version of yourself, the

00:39:12.506 --> 00:39:14.796 A:middle
coworkers with whom you share a

00:39:14.796 --> 00:39:16.686 A:middle
real need for something better,

00:39:16.816 --> 00:39:19.386 A:middle
and you can take that

00:39:19.736 --> 00:39:21.936 A:middle
inspiration and use it to

00:39:21.936 --> 00:39:24.016 A:middle
discover newer and better ways

00:39:24.256 --> 00:39:26.626 A:middle
to connect with people and to

00:39:26.846 --> 00:39:28.746 A:middle
create something really great.

